{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":809,"text":"So, there's an actor\ncalled Dustin Hoffman."},{"time":4285,"text":"And years ago, he made this movie\nwhich some of you may have heard of,"},{"time":7643,"text":"called \"The Graduate.\""},{"time":9261,"text":"And there's two key scenes in that movie."},{"time":12559,"text":"The first one is the seduction scene."},{"time":14677,"text":"I'm not going to talk about that tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16694,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18185,"text":"The second scene is where he's taken out\nby the old guy to the pool,"},{"time":22799,"text":"and as a young college graduate,\nthe old guy basically says one word,"},{"time":27842,"text":"just one word."},{"time":29835,"text":"And of course, all of you know\nwhat that word is."},{"time":32151,"text":"It's \"plastics.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33365,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35190,"text":"And the only problem with that is,\nit was completely the wrong advice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39146,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41229,"text":"Let me tell you why it was so wrong."},{"time":43401,"text":"The word should have been \"silicon.\""},{"time":46163,"text":"And the reason it should have been silicon"},{"time":48211,"text":"is because the basic patents\nfor semiconductors had already been made,"},{"time":53416,"text":"had already been filed,"},{"time":54817,"text":"and they were already building them."},{"time":56606,"text":"So Silicon Valley was just\nbeing built in 1967,"},{"time":59717,"text":"when this movie was released."},{"time":61549,"text":"And the year after the movie was released,"},{"time":63661,"text":"Intel was founded."},{"time":65327,"text":"So had the graduate heard\nthe right one word,"},{"time":68177,"text":"maybe he would have ended up\nonstage -- oh, I don't know --"},{"time":71733,"text":"maybe with these two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72915,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79955,"text":"So as you're thinking of that,"},{"time":82626,"text":"let's see what bit of advice\nwe might want to give"},{"time":86088,"text":"so that your next graduate doesn't become\na Tupperware salesman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89702,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91606,"text":"So in 2015, what word of advice\nwould you give people,"},{"time":95375,"text":"when you took a college\ngraduate out by the pool"},{"time":98040,"text":"and you said one word, just one word?"},{"time":100698,"text":"I think the answer would be \"lifecode.\""},{"time":103312,"text":"So what is \"lifecode?\""},{"time":104495,"text":"Lifecode is the various ways\nwe have of programming life."},{"time":107256,"text":"So instead of programming computers,"},{"time":109115,"text":"we're using things to program viruses"},{"time":111812,"text":"or retroviruses or proteins"},{"time":113860,"text":"or DNA or RNA"},{"time":116501,"text":"or plants or animals,\nor a whole series of creatures."},{"time":119632,"text":"And as you're thinking\nabout this incredible ability"},{"time":122186,"text":"to make life do what you want it to do,"},{"time":124463,"text":"what it's programmed to do,"},{"time":126604,"text":"what you end up doing"},{"time":128421,"text":"is taking what we've been doing\nfor thousands of years,"},{"time":131890,"text":"which is breeding, changing,"},{"time":135035,"text":"mixing, matching"},{"time":137130,"text":"all kinds of life-forms,"},{"time":139163,"text":"and we accelerate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140648,"text":"And this is not something new."},{"time":142172,"text":"This humble mustard weed has been modified"},{"time":145139,"text":"so that if you change it in one way,\nyou get broccoli."},{"time":148714,"text":"And if you change it\nin a second way, you get kale."},{"time":151764,"text":"And if you change it in a third way,"},{"time":153804,"text":"you get cauliflower."},{"time":155662,"text":"So when you go to these\nall-natural, organic markets,"},{"time":159038,"text":"you're really going to a place"},{"time":160642,"text":"where people have been changing\nthe lifecode of plants for a long time."},{"time":165464,"text":"The difference today,"},{"time":166652,"text":"to pick a completely\npolitically neutral term --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168921,"text":"[Intelligent design]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170636,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171817,"text":"We're beginning to practice\nintelligent design."},{"time":174819,"text":"That means that instead\nof doing this at random"},{"time":177081,"text":"and seeing what happens over generations,"},{"time":179161,"text":"we're inserting specific genes,\nwe're inserting specific proteins,"},{"time":182871,"text":"and we're changing lifecode\nfor very deliberate purposes."},{"time":186745,"text":"And that allows us to accelerate\nhow this stuff happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190473,"text":"Let me just give you one example."},{"time":194928,"text":"Some of you occasionally\nmight think about sex."},{"time":199299,"text":"And we kind of take it for granted\nhow we've changed sex."},{"time":202552,"text":"So we think it's perfectly normal\nand natural to change it."},{"time":205960,"text":"What's happened with sex over time is --"},{"time":208323,"text":"normally, sex equals baby, eventually."},{"time":211971,"text":"But in today's world,"},{"time":213505,"text":"sex plus pill equals no baby."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216408,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217916,"text":"And again, we think\nthat's perfectly normal and natural,"},{"time":220678,"text":"but that has not been the case\nfor most of human history."},{"time":223552,"text":"And it's not the case for animals."},{"time":225608,"text":"What it is does is it gives us control,"},{"time":227614,"text":"so sex becomes separate from conception."},{"time":230955,"text":"And as you're thinking\nof the consequences of that,"},{"time":233424,"text":"then we've been playing with stuff"},{"time":235112,"text":"that's a little bit more\nadvanced, like art."},{"time":237447,"text":"Not in the sense\nof painting and sculpture,"},{"time":239549,"text":"but in the sense of assisted\nreproductive technologies."},{"time":245405,"text":"So what are assisted\nreproductive technologies?"},{"time":247865,"text":"Assisted reproductive technologies\nare things like in vitro fertilization."},{"time":252289,"text":"And when you do in vitro fertilization,\nthere's very good reasons to do it."},{"time":255862,"text":"Sometimes you just\ncan't conceive otherwise."},{"time":259622,"text":"But when you do that,"},{"time":260801,"text":"what youâ€™re doing is separating\nsex, conception, baby."},{"time":265786,"text":"So you haven't just taken control\nof when you have a baby,"},{"time":268714,"text":"you've separated when the baby\nand where the baby is fertilized."},{"time":272730,"text":"So you've separated the baby"},{"time":274946,"text":"from the body from the act."},{"time":277332,"text":"And as you're thinking\nof other things we've been doing,"},{"time":280436,"text":"think about twins."},{"time":283029,"text":"So you can freeze sperm,\nyou can freeze eggs,"},{"time":285173,"text":"you can freeze fertilized eggs."},{"time":287778,"text":"And what does that mean?"},{"time":289567,"text":"Well, that's a good thing\nif you're a cancer patient."},{"time":292085,"text":"You're about to go under chemotherapy\nor under radiation,"},{"time":295113,"text":"so you save these things."},{"time":296367,"text":"You don't irradiate them."},{"time":298072,"text":"But if you can save them\nand you can freeze them,"},{"time":300422,"text":"and you can have a surrogate mother,"},{"time":302548,"text":"it means that you've\ndecoupled sex from time."},{"time":305710,"text":"It means you can have twins\nborn -- oh, in 50 years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311287,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"In a hundred years?"},{"time":317342,"text":"Two hundred years?"},{"time":319566,"text":"And these are three\nreally profound changes"},{"time":322377,"text":"that are not, like, future stuff."},{"time":324000,"text":"This is stuff we take for granted today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326911,"text":"So this lifecode stuff\nturns out to be a superpower."},{"time":330520,"text":"It turns out to be this incredibly\npowerful way of changing viruses,"},{"time":334880,"text":"of changing plants, of changing animals,"},{"time":337840,"text":"perhaps even of evolving ourselves."},{"time":340118,"text":"It's something that Steve Gullans and I\nhave been thinking about for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344749,"text":"Let's have some risks."},{"time":346408,"text":"Like every powerful technology,\nlike electricity, like an automobile,"},{"time":350576,"text":"like computers, this stuff\npotentially can be misused."},{"time":354631,"text":"And that scares a lot of people."},{"time":357020,"text":"And as you apply these technologies,"},{"time":358809,"text":"you can even turn human\nbeings into chimeras."},{"time":361815,"text":"Remember the Greek myth\nwhere you mix animals?"},{"time":364378,"text":"Well, some of these treatments"},{"time":366388,"text":"actually end up changing your blood type."},{"time":369406,"text":"Or they'll put male cells\nin a female body or vice versa,"},{"time":374326,"text":"which sounds absolutely horrible"},{"time":375938,"text":"until you realize, the reason\nyou're doing that"},{"time":378239,"text":"is you're substituting bone marrow\nduring cancer treatments."},{"time":381668,"text":"So by taking somebody else's bone marrow,"},{"time":383940,"text":"you may be changing\nsome fundamental aspects of yourself,"},{"time":386656,"text":"but you're also saving your life."},{"time":388568,"text":"And as you're thinking about this stuff,"},{"time":390738,"text":"here's something\nthat happened 20 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393337,"text":"This is Emma Ott."},{"time":394886,"text":"She's a recent college admittee."},{"time":397719,"text":"She's studying accounting."},{"time":399648,"text":"She played two varsity sports.\nShe graduated as a valedictorian."},{"time":403687,"text":"And that's not particularly extraordinary,"},{"time":405731,"text":"except that she's the first human being\nborn to three parents."},{"time":410244,"text":"Why?"},{"time":411419,"text":"Because she had a deadly\nmitochondrial disease"},{"time":413609,"text":"that she might have inherited."},{"time":415118,"text":"So when you swap out a third person's DNA"},{"time":417523,"text":"and you put it in there,"},{"time":419275,"text":"you save the lives of people."},{"time":421840,"text":"But you also are doing\ngermline engineering,"},{"time":424245,"text":"which means her kids,\nif she has kids, will be saved"},{"time":428412,"text":"and won't go through this."},{"time":429846,"text":"And [their] kids will be saved,"},{"time":431361,"text":"and their grandchildren will be saved,"},{"time":433220,"text":"and this passes on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434929,"text":"That makes people nervous."},{"time":436578,"text":"So 20 years ago,\nthe various authorities said,"},{"time":438952,"text":"why don't we study this for a while?"},{"time":441903,"text":"There are risks to doing stuff,\nand there are risks to not doing stuff,"},{"time":445741,"text":"because there were a couple dozen people\nsaved by this technology,"},{"time":449113,"text":"and then we've been thinking about it\nfor the next 20 years."},{"time":453002,"text":"So as we think about it,"},{"time":454209,"text":"as we take the time to say, \"Hey,\nmaybe we should have longer studies,"},{"time":458043,"text":"maybe we should do this,\nmaybe we should do that,\""},{"time":460468,"text":"there are consequences to acting,\nand there are consequences to not acting."},{"time":465203,"text":"Like curing deadly diseases --"},{"time":467688,"text":"which, by the way,\nis completely unnatural."},{"time":470997,"text":"It is normal and natural\nfor humans to be felled"},{"time":474103,"text":"by massive epidemics of polio,\nof smallpox, of tuberculosis."},{"time":478196,"text":"When we put vaccines into people,\nwe are putting unnatural things"},{"time":481863,"text":"into their body"},{"time":483253,"text":"because we think the benefit\noutweighs the risk."},{"time":488129,"text":"Because we've built unnatural plants,\nunnatural animals,"},{"time":491866,"text":"we can feed about seven billion people."},{"time":494413,"text":"We can do things\nlike create new life-forms."},{"time":498302,"text":"And as you create new life-forms,\nagain, that sounds terribly scary"},{"time":501843,"text":"and terribly bothersome,"},{"time":503548,"text":"until you realize that those life-forms\nlive on your dining room table."},{"time":507539,"text":"Those flowers you've got\non your dining room table --"},{"time":510060,"text":"there's not a lot\nthat's natural about them,"},{"time":512253,"text":"because people have been breeding\nthe flowers to make this color,"},{"time":515369,"text":"to be this size, to last for a week."},{"time":517153,"text":"You don't usually give\nyour loved one wildflowers"},{"time":519566,"text":"because they don't last\na whole lot of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524532,"text":"What all this does"},{"time":526421,"text":"is it flips Darwin completely on his head."},{"time":529159,"text":"See, for four billion years,"},{"time":530924,"text":"what lived and died on this planet\ndepended on two principles:"},{"time":534608,"text":"on natural selection and random mutation."},{"time":538016,"text":"And so what lived and died,\nwhat was structured,"},{"time":541167,"text":"has now been flipped on its head."},{"time":544262,"text":"And what we've done"},{"time":545485,"text":"is created this completely\nparallel evolutionary system"},{"time":548120,"text":"where we are practicing unnatural\nselection and non-random mutation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551473,"text":"So let me explain these things."},{"time":553192,"text":"This is natural selection."},{"time":555090,"text":"This is unnatural selection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556519,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559903,"text":"So what happens with this stuff is,"},{"time":562571,"text":"we started breeding wolves\nthousands of years ago"},{"time":565309,"text":"in central Asia to turn them into dogs."},{"time":567523,"text":"And then we started\nturning them into big dogs"},{"time":569841,"text":"and into little dogs."},{"time":571616,"text":"But if you take one of the chihuahuas"},{"time":573427,"text":"you see in the HermÃ¨s bags on Fifth Avenue"},{"time":576299,"text":"and you let it loose on the African plain,"},{"time":578980,"text":"you can watch natural selection happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580988,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586419,"text":"Few things on Earth\nare less natural than a cornfield."},{"time":590188,"text":"You will never, under any scenario,\nwalk through a virgin forest"},{"time":593785,"text":"and see the same plant\ngrowing in orderly rows"},{"time":596494,"text":"at the same time,"},{"time":597842,"text":"nothing else living there."},{"time":600398,"text":"When you do a cornfield,"},{"time":601581,"text":"you're selecting what lives and what dies."},{"time":604080,"text":"And you're doing that\nthrough unnatural selection."},{"time":606443,"text":"It's the same with a wheat field,\nit's the same with a rice field."},{"time":609604,"text":"It's the same with a city,\nit's the same with a suburb."},{"time":612243,"text":"In fact, half the surface of Earth"},{"time":614162,"text":"has been unnaturally engineered"},{"time":615693,"text":"so that what lives and what dies\nthere is what we want,"},{"time":618900,"text":"which is the reason why\nyou don't have grizzly bears"},{"time":621387,"text":"walking through downtown Manhattan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625077,"text":"How about this random mutation stuff?"},{"time":626960,"text":"Well, this is random mutation."},{"time":628427,"text":"This is Antonio Alfonseca."},{"time":630350,"text":"He's otherwise known\nas the Octopus, his nickname."},{"time":633085,"text":"He was the Relief Pitcher\nof the Year in 2000."},{"time":635955,"text":"And he had a random mutation\nthat gave him six fingers"},{"time":638743,"text":"on each hand,"},{"time":640995,"text":"which turns out to be really useful\nif you're a pitcher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643661,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646119,"text":"How about non-random mutation?"},{"time":648415,"text":"A non-random mutation is beer."},{"time":651412,"text":"It's wine. It's yogurt."},{"time":653928,"text":"How many times have you walked\nthrough the forest"},{"time":656288,"text":"and found all-natural cheese?"},{"time":658859,"text":"Or all-natural yogurt?"},{"time":661046,"text":"So we've been engineering this stuff."},{"time":662855,"text":"Now, the interesting thing is,"},{"time":664347,"text":"we get to know the stuff better."},{"time":666364,"text":"We found one of the single most powerful\ngene-editing instruments,"},{"time":670101,"text":"CRISPR, inside yogurt."},{"time":673028,"text":"And as we start engineering cells,"},{"time":675042,"text":"we're producing eight out of the top 10\npharmaceutical products,"},{"time":680246,"text":"including the stuff that you use\nto treat arthritis,"},{"time":682795,"text":"which is the number one\nbest-selling drug, Humira."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685985,"text":"So this lifecode stuff."},{"time":688229,"text":"It really is a superpower."},{"time":690156,"text":"It really is a way of programming stuff,"},{"time":692094,"text":"and there's nothing\nthat's going to change us"},{"time":694675,"text":"more than this lifecode."},{"time":697597,"text":"So as you're thinking of lifecode,"},{"time":699602,"text":"let's think of five principles"},{"time":702231,"text":"as to how we start guiding,"},{"time":704110,"text":"and I'd love you to give me more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706315,"text":"So, principle number one:"},{"time":708282,"text":"we have to take responsibility\nfor this stuff."},{"time":711042,"text":"The reason we have to take responsibility"},{"time":713617,"text":"is because we're in charge."},{"time":715002,"text":"These aren't random mutations."},{"time":716939,"text":"This is what we are doing,\nwhat we are choosing."},{"time":719266,"text":"It's not, \"Stuff happened.\""},{"time":720989,"text":"It didn't happen at random."},{"time":722486,"text":"It didn't come down\nby a verdict of somebody else."},{"time":725114,"text":"We engineer this stuff,"},{"time":726955,"text":"and it's the Pottery Barn rule:\nyou break it, you own it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730962,"text":"Principle number two:"},{"time":732515,"text":"we have to recognize and celebrate\ndiversity in this stuff."},{"time":735667,"text":"There have been at least\n33 versions of hominids"},{"time":738825,"text":"that have walked around this Earth."},{"time":740912,"text":"Most all of them went extinct except us."},{"time":743804,"text":"But the normal and natural\nstate of this Earth"},{"time":745989,"text":"is we have various versions of humans\nwalking around at the same time,"},{"time":749400,"text":"which is why most of us\nhave some Neanderthal in us."},{"time":752559,"text":"Some of us have some Denisova in us."},{"time":755023,"text":"And some in Washington\nhave a lot more of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757396,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759998,"text":"Principle number three:"},{"time":761907,"text":"we have to respect other people's choices."},{"time":764608,"text":"Some people will choose to never alter."},{"time":766907,"text":"Some people will choose to alter all."},{"time":768741,"text":"Some people will choose\nto alter plants but not animals."},{"time":771391,"text":"Some people will choose\nto alter themselves."},{"time":773466,"text":"Some people will choose\nto evolve themselves."},{"time":775753,"text":"Diversity is not a bad thing,"},{"time":777346,"text":"because even though we think\nof humans as very diverse,"},{"time":780012,"text":"we came so close to extinction"},{"time":782321,"text":"that all of us descend\nfrom a single African mother"},{"time":784960,"text":"and the consequence of that"},{"time":786309,"text":"is there's more genetic diversity\nin 55 African chimpanzees"},{"time":790838,"text":"than there are in seven billion humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794254,"text":"Principle number four:"},{"time":797079,"text":"we should take about\na quarter of the Earth"},{"time":799780,"text":"and only let Darwin run the show there."},{"time":802981,"text":"It doesn't have to be contiguous,"},{"time":804606,"text":"doesn't have to all be tied together."},{"time":806404,"text":"It should be part\nin the oceans, part on land."},{"time":808634,"text":"But we should not run every\nevolutionary decision on this planet."},{"time":812474,"text":"We want to have\nour evolutionary system running."},{"time":814936,"text":"We want to have Darwin's\nevolutionary system running."},{"time":817537,"text":"And it's just really important to have\nthese two things running in parallel"},{"time":821237,"text":"and not overwhelm evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822778,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":830307,"text":"Last thing I'll say."},{"time":832654,"text":"This is the single most exciting\nadventure human beings have been on."},{"time":835940,"text":"This is the single greatest superpower\nhumans have ever had."},{"time":839005,"text":"It would be a crime for you\nnot to participate in this stuff"},{"time":841897,"text":"because you're scared of it,"},{"time":843333,"text":"because you're hiding from it."},{"time":845096,"text":"You can participate in the ethics.\nYou can participate in the politics."},{"time":848491,"text":"You can participate in the business."},{"time":850264,"text":"You can participate in just thinking\nabout where medicine is going,"},{"time":853446,"text":"where industry is going,"},{"time":854631,"text":"where we're going to take the world."},{"time":856458,"text":"It would be a crime for all of us"},{"time":858347,"text":"not to be aware when somebody\nshows up at a swimming pool"},{"time":862429,"text":"and says one word, just one word,"},{"time":865499,"text":"if you don't listen\nif that word is \"lifecode.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":867922,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869224,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}